# Risotto

## Ingredients

### Core

* 1 ½ cups 
* 4 cups chicken stock (kept warm)
* 1 shallot, finely diced
* 2 tablespoons butter
* Salt and black pepper to taste
* ½ cup dry white wine
* ½ cup grated Parmigiano-Reggiano
* Mushroom (optional)

### Extra
* 1/4 cup grated Parmigiano-Reggiano


## Instructions

1. In a pot, warm the stock and keep it at a low simmer. If using saffron, steep it in a bit of hot stock.
2. In a heavy pan, heat butter over medium heat. Add shallots cook on medium for 2-3minutes.
3. Add rice, stirring constantly for 2 minutes until grains are glossy and slightly translucent on the edges.
4. Pour in white wine and cook until mostly evaporated.
5. Begin adding hot stock, one ladle at a time, stirring often. Add the next ladle only when the previous one is nearly absorbed.
6. Continue for 18–22 minutes until rice is al dente and creamy. Half way through, add Parmigiano-Reggiano or any mushrooms, parsley
7. Remove from heat. Stir in cold butter and Parmesan to “mantecatura” (make it creamy). Let rest 1 minute.
